The main objective of this study is to elaborate, in the neonatal period, a prognostic score for the development of neurological and sensorineural sequelae at 1 year in neonates infected in utero by cytomegalovirus.

 This score will be based on clinical, imaging and biological evaluations.

 The second objective of the study is to estimate the prevalence of this infection in France and to describe its epidemiology through the screening of 10,000 consecutive neonates.

